signature_matches.name: check mutex
signature_matches.description: host-interaction/mutex
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: check mutex
    namespace: host-interaction/mutex
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
    scope: basic block
    mbc:
      - Process::Check Mutex [C0043]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-01.dll_:0x10001010
  features:
    - and:
      - or:
        - api: kernel32.OpenMutex
        - match: create mutex
        - api: System.Threading.Mutex::OpenExisting
        - api: System.Threading.Mutex::TryOpenExisting
      - optional:
        - or:
          - api: kernel32.GetLastError
          - number: 2 = ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND
          - number: 0xB7 = ERROR_ALREADY_EXISTS

signature_matches.name: get OS version

rule:
  meta:
    name: get OS version
    authors:
      - "@mr-tz"
    lib: true
    scope: function
    examples:
      - 493167E85E45363D09495D0841C30648:0x401000
      - 5f66b82558ca92e54e77f216ef4c066c:0x44580A
  features:
    - or:
      - api: RtlGetVersion
      - api: ntoskrnl.PsGetVersion
      - api: GetVersion
      - api: GetVersionEx
      - api: VerifyVersionInfo
      - api: VerSetConditionMask
      - api: RtlGetNtVersionNumbers
      - api: GetProductInfo
      - and:
        - match: PEB access
        - or:
          - and:
            - arch: i386
            - or:
              - offset: 0xA4 = PEB->OSMajorVersion
              - offset: 0xA8 = PEB->OSMinorVersion
              - offset: 0xAC = PEB->OSBuildNumber
          - and:
            - arch: amd64
            - or:
              - offset: 0x118 = PEB->OSMajorVersion
              - offset: 0x11C = PEB->OSMinorVersion
              - offset: 0x120 = PEB->OSBuildNumber

signature_matches.name: link many functions at runtime
signature_matches.description: linking/runtime-linking
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: link many functions at runtime
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - joakim@intezer.com
    scope: function
    att&ck:
      - Execution::Shared Modules [T1129]
    examples:
      - b7b5e1253710d8927cbe07d52d2d2e10:0x401000
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - os: windows
        - match: link function at runtime on Windows
        - or:
          - count(api(kernel32.GetProcAddress)): 5 or more
          - count(api(ntdll.LdrGetProcedureAddress)): 5 or more
      - and:
        - os: linux
        - match: link function at runtime on Linux
        - or:
          - count(api(dlsym)): 5 or more
          - count(api(dlvsym)): 5 or more

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Regsvr32 DLL Execution With Uncommon Extension
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a "regsvr32" execution where the DLL doesn't contain a common file extension.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Access To Windows DPAPI Master Keys By Uncommon Applications
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects file access requests to the the Windows Data Protection API Master keys by an uncommon application.
This can be a sign of credential stealing. Example case would be usage of mimikatz "dpapi::masterkey" function

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious File Access to Browser Credential Storage
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects file access to browser credential storage paths by non-browser processes, which may indicate credential access attempts.
Adversaries may attempt to access browser credential storage to extract sensitive information such as usernames and passwords or cookies.
This behavior is often commonly observed in credential stealing malware.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: frack113, X__Junior (Nextron Systems), Swachchhanda Shrawan Poudel (Nextron Systems), Parth-FourCore

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the execution of the "jsc.exe" (JScript Compiler).
Attacker might abuse this in order to compile JScript files on the fly and bypassing application whitelisting.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: ADS Zone.Identifier Deleted By Uncommon Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the deletion of the "Zone.Identifier" ADS by an uncommon process. Attackers can leverage this in order to bypass security restrictions that make use of the ADS such as Microsoft Office apps.
